    {
      "note_no": "3598",
      "note": "In any apparent conflict of duties our standard should be Allah's Will, as declared to us by His command. That is the way of those who love Allah and their motive in disobedience to parents or human authority where disobedience is necessary by Allah's Law, is not self-willed rebellion or defiance, but love of Allah, which means the true love of man in the highest sense of the word. And the reason we should give is, \"Both you and I have to return to Allah: therefore not only must I follow Allah's Will, but you must command nothing against Allah's will.\""
    },
